            <title>[JDK-8317736] Stream::handleReset locks twice</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8317736</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8308310&quot; title=&quot;HttpClient: Avoid logging or locking from within synchronized blocks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8308310&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8308310&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a reentrant stateLock but also a regression. In Stream::handleReset the lock is locked twice.</description>
