                            <comment id="14616758" author="dfuchs" created="Mon, 9 Oct 2023 09:43:24 -0700"  >jdk21u-fix-request:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This fixes a regression that was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8308310&quot; title=&quot;HttpClient: Avoid logging or locking from within synchronized blocks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8308310&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8308310&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which was pushed to JDK 21. Without this fix, reception of a RESET might cause a thread to block and forever and prevent a request to terminate. The fix is trivial (a one liner: finally should have called stateLock.unlock(), not stateLock.lock() again).</comment>
